{"lemma":"رَجْعُ","slug":"رَجْعُ","root":"ر.ج.ع","root_slug":"ر-ج-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَجْع","root":"رجع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":23},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14878","n14886","n14888","n14889"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to return, to come back","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَنْ أَرْجِعَ مَعَهُ.","english":"I won’t go back with him."},{"text":"وَلَمَّا رَجَعَ مُوسَىٰٓ إِلَىٰ قَوْمِهِ غَضْبَانَ أَسِفًا قَالَ بِئْسَمَا خَلَفْتُمُونِي مِنْ بَعْدِيٓ","english":"When Moses returned to his people, ˹totally˺ furious and sorrowful, he said, “What an evil thing you committed in my absence!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to revert","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to resume","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to look up in a book","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to consult","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to derive, to stem","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to depend","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to belong (by right)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to refrain, to desist","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to revoke, to countermand","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to withdraw","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"رَجَعَ عَنْ رَأْيِهِ","english":"He changed his mind."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn against","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reduce","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to claim","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to entail, to imply","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to do well, to be successful","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to repent","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَأَخَذْنَاهُمْ بِالْعَذَابِ لَعَلَّهُمْ يَرْجِعُونَ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to send back, to return","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to resurrect, to bring back to life","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّهُ عَلَى رَجْعِهِ لَقَادِرٌ"},{"text":"حَتَّى إِذَا جَاءَ أَحَدَهُمُ الْمَوْتُ قَالَ رَبِّ ٱرْجِعُونِ لَعَلِّي أَعْمَلُ صَالِحًا فِيمَا تَرَكْتُ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to say إِنَّا لِلّٰهِ وَإِنَّا إِلَيْهِ رَاجِعُونَ (ʔinnā lillāhi waʔinnā ʔilayhi rājiʕūna)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to send back"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَجَعَ (rajaʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رِجَاع (rijāʕ, “nose rein of a camel”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ra.d͡ʒa.ʕa/","/rad͡ʒ.d͡ʒa.ʕa/","/rad͡ʒʕ/","/ru.d͡ʒuʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14878","headword_ar":"رَجَعَ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwEN","text_ar":"رُجُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) but the former is that which commonly obtains and is agreeable with analogy as inf. n. of the intrans. v., and the latter as inf. n. of the trans. v., (MF, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojaEN","text_ar":"مَرْجَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) which is anomalous, because inf. ns. [of this kind] of verbs of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1038},{"kind":"text","text":"aor. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEilu","text_ar":"يَفْعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are [by rule] only with fet-h [to the medial radical], (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojiEapN","text_ar":"مَرْجِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is in like manner anomalous, (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaY","text_ar":"رُجْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) [not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEFY","text_ar":"رُجْعًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Lexicons of Golius and Freytag,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned; he went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came, back"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to the same place, or person, or (assumed tropical:)  state, or (assumed tropical:)  occupation, or (assumed tropical:)  action, or (assumed tropical:)  saying, &c.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he reverted; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnoSarafa","text_ar":"انْصَرَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwEN","text_ar":"رُجُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning to a former place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 196;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning to that from which was the commencement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which the commencement is supposed to have been, whether it be a place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a saying, and whether the returning be by the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person or thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a part thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by an action thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) Hence the saying in the Kur [lxiii. 8],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay^ino rajaEonaA A_ilaY Almadiynapi","text_ar":"لَيِنْ رَجَعْنَا اـِلَى المَدِينَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily if we return to the city"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib.) And [in the same, xii. 63,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falam~aA rajaEuwA A_ilaY A^abiyhimo","text_ar":"فَلَمَّا رَجَعُوا اـِلَى اَبِيهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when they returned to their father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Idem.) And in the same, [vi. 164, and xxxix. 9,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a A_ilaY rab~ikumo marojiEukumo","text_ar":"ثُمَّ اـِلَى رَبِّكُمْ مَرْجِعُكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then unto your Lord shall be your return"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) the like of which occurs in the same, vi. 60: but it may be either from [the intrans. inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwEN","text_ar":"رُجُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or from [the trans.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib:) it cannot be a n. of place, because it is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and also because it occurs in the Kur [v. 53, &c.], followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamiyEFA","text_ar":"جَمِيعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a denotative of state: (L:) in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ujoEaY","text_ar":"الرُّجْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs in the Kur xcvi. 8. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEati AlmaroA^apu A_ilaY","text_ar":"رَجَعَتِ المَرْاَةُ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholihaA","text_ar":"اَهْلِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman returned to her family"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of the death of her husband or by reason of divorcement. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A_ilaY AlS~iH~api","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اـِلَى الصِّحَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to soundness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"health"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaraDi","text_ar":"المَرَضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sickness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY HaAlapi Alfaqori","text_ar":"اـِلَى حَالَةِ الفَقْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the state of poverty"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlginaY","text_ar":"الغِنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kull p. 196.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa","text_ar":"رَجَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eawodahu EalaY badoy^ihi","text_ar":"عَوْدَهُ عَلَى بَدْيِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned in the way by which he had come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull ibid.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa mino safarihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ مِنْ سَفَرِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned from his journey."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa Eani","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^imori","text_ar":"الاِمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relinquished, the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 197.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa Eani","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~anobi","text_ar":"الذَّنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He relinquished sin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repented;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa","text_ar":"رَجَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, agreeably with the usage in the Kur iii. 65, &c. (Er-Rághib.) ―         -b8-  [Several other phrases, in which this verb occurs, will be found in other arts.: as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa EalaY Zahorihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَلَى ظَهْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zhr","text_ar":"ظهر"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEotu AlqahoqaraY","text_ar":"رَجَعْتُ القَهْقَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qhqr","text_ar":"قهقر"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa darajahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَ دَرَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and variations thereof, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drj","text_ar":"درج"},{"kind":"text","text":": &c.] ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A_ilayohi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[sometimes signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa Ealayohi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned against him; he returned to attack him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saram~niY vum~a rajaEa yakal~imuniY","text_ar":"صَرَمّنِى ثُمَّ رَجَعَ يَكَلِّمُنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to speak to me; then he returned to speaking to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAlafaniY vum~a rajaEa A_ilaY","text_ar":"خَالَفَنِى ثُمَّ رَجَعَ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawoliY","text_ar":"قَوْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opposed me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disagreed with me; then he returned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had regard, to my saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA rujiEa A_ilayohi fiY xaTobK A_il~aA kafaY","text_ar":"مَا رُجِعَ اـِلَيْهِ فِى خَطْبٍ اـِلَّا كَفَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Re course was not had to him in an affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affliction, but he sufficed."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A_ilayohi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had recourse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he recurred, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa bihi EalaY $ariykihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ بِهِ عَلَى شَرِيكِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a claim for restitution of it upon his co-partner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlT","text_ar":"خلط"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And [in like manner you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Algariymi","text_ar":"عَلَى الغَرِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotajaEa","text_ar":"اِرْتَجَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almut~ahami","text_ar":"المُتَّهَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sued, prosecuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a demand upon, the debtor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the suspected, for his right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: [in which it is said, immediately before this, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjE","text_ar":"ارتجع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa","text_ar":"رَجَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa Alkalobu fiY qayoy^ihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ الكَلْبُ فِى قَيْيِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dog returned to his vomit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and ate it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b15-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa fiY hibatihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ فِى هِبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took back his gift; repossessed himself of it; restored it to his possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjEhA","text_ar":"ارتجعها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstrjEhA","text_ar":"استرجعها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu Al$~aYo'","text_ar":"مِنْهُ الشَّىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstrjE","text_ar":"استرجع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took back from him the thing which he had given to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b16-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa fiY qawolihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ فِى قَوْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Hukomihi","text_ar":"فِى حُكْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He retracted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revoked, his saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentence."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yarojiEu A_ilaY manoSibi SidoqK","text_ar":"هُوَ يَرْجِعُ اـِلَى مَنْصِبِ صِدْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He traces back his lineage to an excellent origin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nSb","text_ar":"نصب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b18-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarojiEu A_ilaY maEonaY ka*aA","text_ar":"يَرْجِعُ اـِلَى مَعْنَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a word used in a certain sense)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is referrible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reducible, to such a meaning."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurojiEu A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"يُرْجِعُ اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a word, also means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It relates to such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., to such another word, in grammatical construction.] ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A_ilaY qadori ka*aA","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اـِلَى قَدْرِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(wine when cooked)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became reduced to such a quantity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=la","text_ar":"ا=لَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Awl","text_ar":"اول"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa AlHawoDu A_ilaY A_izaAy^ihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ الحَوْضُ اـِلَى اـِزَايِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water of the trough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank, became much in quantity"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it returned to the height of the place whence it poured in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b21-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAEN","text_ar":"رِجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is an inf. n. of this verb, (L,) and is used as signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"of birds"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after"},{"kind":"text","text":"their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"migrating to a hot country."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEati AlT~ayoru AlqawaATiEu","text_ar":"رَجَعَتِ الطَّيْرُ القَوَاطِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAEN","text_ar":"رِجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The migratory birds returned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b22-  Also inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEato","text_ar":"رَجَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a-she camel, and of a she-ass, signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She raised her tail, and compressed her two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTorayohaA","text_ar":"قُطْرَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cast forth her urine in repeated discharges, so that she was imagined to be pregnant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then failed of fulfilling her"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S: [in some copies of which, as is said in the TA, the inf. n. of the verb in this sense is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujuwE","text_ar":"رُجُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she conceived, and then failed of fulfilling her promise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because she who does so goes back from what is hoped of her: (TA:) or, said of a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she cast forth her fœtus in an imperfect state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA,) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her embryo in a fluid state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an unformed state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAEN","text_ar":"رِجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xdj","text_ar":"خدج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjiEN","text_ar":"رَاجِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]       -A2- , (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojaEN","text_ar":"مَرْجَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojiEN","text_ar":"مَرْجِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to return, go back, come back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert; sent back, turned back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sarafahu","text_ar":"صَرَفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArjEhu","text_ar":"ارجعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) but the former is the more chaste word, and is that which is used in the Kur-án, in ix. 84 [and other places]: (Msb:) the latter is of the dial. of Hudheyl; (S, Msb;) and is said by MF to be of weak authority, and bad; but [SM says,] I do not find this asserted by any of the leading authorities: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjEhu","text_ar":"ارتجعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, signifies [the same, i. e.] the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in like manner followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Thus in the Kur ix. 84, referred to above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_ino rajaEaka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"فَاـِنْ رَجَعَكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if God make thee to return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restore thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa fulaAnN EaliY A^anofi baEiyirhi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ فُلَانٌ عَلِى اَنْفِ بَعِيِرهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one put back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restored, the nose-rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxiTaAma","text_ar":"الخِطَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being understood]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the nose of his camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"it having become displaced. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljawaAba","text_ar":"الجَوَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to me the answer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA: [in the latter of which, this is said to be tropical; but when a written answer is meant, it is evidently not so.]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEotu AlkalaAma","text_ar":"رَجَعْتُ الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I returned the speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I repeated it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rebutted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rejected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repudiated, it, in reply,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replication;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radadotuhu","text_ar":"رَدَدْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [In like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarojiEu baEoDuhumo","text_ar":"يَرْجِعُ بَعْضُهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY baEoDK Alqawola","text_ar":"اـِلَى بَعْضٍ القَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxxiv. 30], means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Holding a colloquy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"debate, one with another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) [or it means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rebutting one another's sayings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blaming one another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajoEu","text_ar":"الرَّجْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEu Ald~aAb~api yadayohaA fiY Als~ayori","text_ar":"رَجْعُ الدَّابَّةِ يَدَيْهَا فِى السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stepping of the beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her returning her fore legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drawing the fore feet backwards towards the body, by lifting them high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in going;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arojiyEu","text_ar":"التَّرْجِيعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojiyEu Ald~aAb~pi yadayohaA fiY Als~ayori","text_ar":"تَرْجِيعُ الدَّابّةِ يَدَيْهَا فِى السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) signifies the same: (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a beast's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lifting high, the fore foot and hind foot, in going."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAb~apu yadayohaA fiY","text_ar":"الدَّابَّةُ يَدَيْهَا فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raj~aEati","text_ar":"رَجَّعَتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayori","text_ar":"السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beast stepped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEat","text_ar":"رَجَعَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEu AlwaA$mapi","text_ar":"رَجْعُ الوَاشمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarojayEuhaA","text_ar":"تَرْجَيعُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female tattooer's making marks"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K: *) [or rather, as the former phrase is explained in the EM p. 143, “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her retracing"},{"kind":"text","text":"”"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those marks"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines, and renewing their blackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alnaqo$a","text_ar":"النَقْشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raj~aEa","text_ar":"رَجَّعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwa$oma","text_ar":"الوَشْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He retraced the marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines, of the variegated work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tattooing, and renewed their blackness, one time after another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbapa","text_ar":"الكِتَابَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raj~aEa","text_ar":"رَجَّعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEahaA","text_ar":"رَجَعَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He retraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"renewed, the writing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa naAqapF","text_ar":"رَجَعَ نَاقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjEhA","text_ar":"ارتجعها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trj~EhA","text_ar":"ترجّعها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He purchased a she-camel with the price of another that he sold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he purchased a she-camel with the price of a he-camel that he sold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaEN","text_ar":"رِجَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is app. an inf. n., signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selling males and purchasing females:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlFA","text_ar":"مَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjE","text_ar":"ارتجع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sold the aged and the younglings of his came's, and purchased such as were in a state of youthful vigour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sold the males, and purchased females:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotijaAEN","text_ar":"اِرْتِجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"selling a thing, and purchasing in its place what one imagines to be more youthful, and better:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh in another place:) regard is bad, therein, to the meaning of a return, virtual, or understood, though not real: (Er-Rághib:) also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilFA","text_ar":"اـِبِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArjE","text_ar":"ارجع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sold old and weak camels, and purchased such as were in a state of youthful vigour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sold male camels, and purchased females:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilFA","text_ar":"اـِبِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjE","text_ar":"ارتجع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA_ibilihi","text_ar":"بِاـِبِلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took camels in exchange for his camels:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1039},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotijaAEN","text_ar":"اِرْتِجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking one in the place, and with the price, of two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa AlEalafu fiY Ald~aAb~api","text_ar":"رَجَعَ العَلَفُ فِى الدَّابَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fodder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food, produced an effect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"showed its effect, upon the beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa kalaAmiY fiyhi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ كَلَامِى فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My speech produced a beneficial effect upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","MF","TA","S","K","L","Mgh","AZ","Bd","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n14886","headword_ar":"رَجْعٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; originally an inf. n.: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa","text_ar":"رَجَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEapN","text_ar":"رَجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur [lxxxvi. 11],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~amaA='i *aAti","text_ar":"وَالسَّمَا=ءِ ذَاتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajoEi","text_ar":"الرَّجْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the heaven that hath rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Bd:) because God returns it time after time: or because the clouds raise the water from the seas and then return it to the earth; and if so, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsmA'","text_ar":"اسماء"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be meant the clouds: (Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain after rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) because it returns time after time; or because it is repeated, and returns, every year: (TA:) or the said words of the Kur mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the heaven that returns in every revolution to the place whence it moved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it gives back the water that it takes. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Accord. to El-Asadee, as recorded by AHeyth, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thunder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az.) ―         -b6-  Accord. to some, in the passage of the Kur cited above, (S, TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Profit, benefit, advantage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good return."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa liY mino fulaAnK rajoEN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِى مِنْ فُلَانٍ رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no profit to me from such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa A_il~aA sajoEN layosa taHotahu rajoEN","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ اـِلَّا سَجْعٌ لَيْسَ تَحْتَهُ رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is nothing but rhyming prose, beneath which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be found"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no profit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b7-  Accord. to Ks, in the ex. cited above from the Kur, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place that retains water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pool of water left by a torrent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) because of the rain that is in it; or because of its fluctuating to and fro in its place; (Er-Rághib;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiyEN","text_ar":"رَجِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjiEapN","text_ar":"رَاجِعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl. as above: (S:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which the torrent has extended itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimotad~a","text_ar":"اِمْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Lth and the O and K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which it has returned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reverted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Airotad~a","text_ar":"اِرْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to AHn,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then passed through:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, AHn, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEaAnN","text_ar":"رِجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAEN","text_ar":"رِجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or this last, accord. to some, is a sing., having the signification next preceding the last here mentioned, and is found prefixed to its syn., namely"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadiyr","text_ar":"غَدِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", to show that it is used in this sense, and is qualified by a sing. epithet, namely"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iE","text_ar":"رَايِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but some say that it is thus qualified becanse it has a form which is that of a sing. noun: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEN","text_ar":"رَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in general;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and a sword is likened to it, to denote its whiteness: (AO, S: [but accord. to the latter, in this case it signifies “ a pool of water left by a torrent ”:]) and also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract of ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land, in which the torrent has extended itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) but this, it should be observed, is a repetition of the saying of Lth mentioned above: (TA:) and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is above a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taloEap","text_ar":"تَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (K, TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest, part thereof, before its water collects together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujoEaAnN","text_ar":"رُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"season,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [because it returns year after year;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiyEN","text_ar":"رَجِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b10-  (assumed tropical:)  The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"membrane called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girps","text_ar":"غِرةس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is in the belly of the woman, and which comes forth upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, the head of the child."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiyEN","text_ar":"رَجِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places, in the latter part of the paragraph. ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN najiyHu Alr~ajoEi","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ نَجِيحُ الرَّجْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajiyEi","text_ar":"الرَّجِيعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sword which penetrates into the thing that is struck with it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it is quickly drawn back"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoEu Alkatifi","text_ar":"رَجْعُ الكَتِفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojiEN","text_ar":"مَرْجِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Bd","TA","K","Lth","AHn","O","AO"]},{"entry_id":"n14888","headword_ar":"رُجَعٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14889","headword_ar":"رِجَعٌ","root":"rjE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa naAqapF","text_ar":"رَجَعَ نَاقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoEapN","text_ar":"رِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}